      • SnapshotStateImpl

        protected SnapshotStateImpl(java.util.Map<Hash,java.lang.Long> balances)
        Creates a SnapshotState from the passed in Map by storing the mapping in its private property. While most of the other methods are public, this constructor is protected since we do not want to allow the manual creation of SnapshotState's outside of the snapshot logic.
        Parameters:
        balances - map with the addresses associated to their balance

      • hasCorrectSupply

        public boolean hasCorrectSupply()
        Checks if the state of the ledger has the correct supply by adding the balances of all addresses and comparing it against the expected value. It doesn't make sense to call this functions on differential states (returned by SnapshotState.patchedState(SnapshotStateDiff) that are used to check the consistency of patches.
        Specified by:
        hasCorrectSupply in interface SnapshotState
        Returns:
        true if the supply is correct and false otherwise

      • applyStateDiff

        public void applyStateDiff(SnapshotStateDiff diff)
                    throws SnapshotException
        This method applies the given SnapshotStateDiff to the current balances. Before applying the SnapshotStateDiff we check if it is consistent.
        Specified by:
        applyStateDiff in interface SnapshotState
        Parameters:
        diff - the balance changes that should be applied to this state.
        Throws:

      • patchedState

        public SnapshotState patchedState(SnapshotStateDiff snapshotStateDiff)
        This method creates a differential SnapshotState that contains the resulting balances of only the addresses that are modified by the given SnapshotStateDiff. It can be used to check if the modifications by a SnapshotStateDiff will result in a consistent State where all modified addresses are still positive. Even though this State can be consistent, it will most probably not return true if we call SnapshotState.hasCorrectSupply() since the unmodified addresses are missing.
        Specified by:
        patchedState in interface SnapshotState
        Parameters:
        snapshotStateDiff - the balance patches that we want to apply
        Returns:
        a differential SnapshotState that contains the resulting balances of all modified addresses
